abstract: Members of the party establishment who oppose Bernie Sanders have had discussions about how to handle his candidacy, while others warn of a schism within the party.
snippet: Members of the party establishment who oppose Bernie Sanders have had discussions about how to handle his candidacy, while others warn of a schism within the party.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — When Leah Daughtry, a former Democratic Party official, addressed a closed-door gathering of about 100 wealthy liberal donors in San Francisco last month, all it took was a review of the 2020 primary rules to throw a scare in them.

abstract: The museum said that it was “deeply concerned” about renting the space for an event to honor someone whose environmental policies had been widely criticized.
snippet: The museum said that it was “deeply concerned” about renting the space for an event to honor someone whose environmental policies had been widely criticized.
lead_paragraph: The American Museum of Natural History said Monday that it would no longer host an event at the museum by an outside organization that was to have honored President Jair Bolsonaro of Brazil, whose environmental policies have come under fire.

headline_main: DealBook Briefing: Goldman Says Trump Could Squeak a Win in 2020

abstract: How much will the company be valued at? What can go wrong? Who stands to get rich? What does it mean for other I. P. O.s? Let us answer all those questions and more.
snippet: How much will the company be valued at? What can go wrong? Who stands to get rich? What does it mean for other I. P. O.s? Let us answer all those questions and more.
lead_paragraph: Good Sunday morning, and welcome to a special edition of the DealBook Briefing, where we’ll take a deep dive into Pinterest’s upcoming public offering. It’s the second of many decacorns — $10 billion-plus start-ups — to go public this year. And it could be an indicator of what’s to come during the rest of 2019. (Was this email forwarded to you? Sign up here.)

abstract: The museum said it was “deeply concerned” that the event it is hosting will honor Brazil’s president, whose environmental policies have drawn criticism.
snippet: The museum said it was “deeply concerned” that the event it is hosting will honor Brazil’s president, whose environmental policies have drawn criticism.
lead_paragraph: The American Museum of Natural History says it is exploring its options after discovering that the honoree at a gala to which it rented space next month will be President Jair Bolsonaro of Brazil, whose environmental policies have come under fire.

headline_main: DealBook Briefing: Uber’s Growth Is Slowing

abstract: As the situation drags on, the aerospace giant and the airlines that rely on its planes have been scrambling to adjust, and the costs are growing.
snippet: As the situation drags on, the aerospace giant and the airlines that rely on its planes have been scrambling to adjust, and the costs are growing.
lead_paragraph: In the 22 months that Boeing’s 737 Max flew commercially before it was grounded, the jet became the company’s flagship as well as an integral part of the global aviation system, and the American economy.

headline_main: How Big Business Is Hedging Against the Apocalypse

abstract: The chiefs of seven huge American banks testified on Capitol Hill yesterday, and talked regulation, Russia, recession and more.

headline_main: DealBook Briefing: What Bank C.E.O.s Said to Congress

abstract: The digital world is not designed to keep women safe. New regulations should be.
snippet: The digital world is not designed to keep women safe. New regulations should be.
lead_paragraph: Like too many women, I’ve been harassed online. The harasser described in explicit detail how he intended to violate me, though somehow his threats didn’t violate Twitter’s terms of service. Twitter, despite my repeated reports, did nothing.
